@@gBRAWLER@@W

@@gHistory@@W
  The Brawler path has no founding text, no academy, and no claim to ancient
  wisdom -- it arose from the fighting pits of the harbor districts, where
  survival demanded adaptation rather than theory. Early Brawlers were simply
  the best fighters in contested spaces: people who had learned through
  accumulated hard experience exactly how much punishment a body could absorb
  and deliver, and who had mastered by instinct the grinding attrition that
  breaks opponents the mind alone cannot. Over time the best survivors passed
  their methods to apprentices not through formal instruction but through
  demonstration. Every technique in the Brawler's arsenal has been tested at
  full force against opponents who were trying to kill someone. The ones that
  survived that test are the only ones still taught.

Brawlers are ruthless close-range enforcers who overwhelm opponents through
repetition, pressure, and punishing body mechanics.

